
[1]securely

   SECU'RELY, adv.

   1. Without danger; safely; as, to pass a river on ice securely. But
   safely is generally used.

   2. Without fear or apprehension; carelessly; in an unguarded state; in
   confidence of safety.

   His daring foe securely him defied. Milton.

   Devise not evil against thy neighbor, seeing he dwelleth securely by
   thee. Prov. 3.
